https://github.com/apache/incubator-openwhisk/blob/master/tools/cli/go-whisk-cli/commands/action.go#L596

we can perhaps use pointer instead of string copying to make it more faster.

@darrenmothersele Everything on your list _except_ mcrypt is included. 

I have not included mcrypt it is deprecated in PHP 7.1 as it has been unmaintained since [2007](https://sourceforge.net/projects/mcrypt/files/Libmcrypt/) and abandoned since [2011](https://sourceforge.net/p/mcrypt/mailman/mcrypt-developers/).

It is completely removed from PHP 7.2 and I don't see any point in including it.

@rabbah 
PG2 1808 reapproved and proved no [ERROR] message indicating a resent message as outlined in this PR.

note the change to `Invoker.scala`

Look in InvokerSupervision. It actually tried to invoke an action. If that fails it will make the invoker unhealthy. Yes some requests might get queued on that invoker while the health protocol completes but eventually it should detect a failing invoker. 

    /** Scheduler to send test activations when the invoker is unhealthy. */
    onTransition {
        case _ -> UnHealthy => {
            invokeTestAction()
            setTimer(InvokerActor.timerName, Tick, 1.minute, true)
        }
        case UnHealthy -> _ => cancelTimer(InvokerActor.timerName)
    }

But I now suspect there's a bug in the protocol in the case of a missing active ack. I have to check again in the morning and confirm if a test exists in that case. 

I think your change is actually undesirable. In that the invoker pool can be full because of load - that should not mark the invoker unavailable.
